withTableLock

public TableSelect.TableJoin<E> withTableLock(boolean lockEnabled)
Description copied from interface: TableSelect
If set to true, the select will set the ReentrantReadWriteLock.ReadLock on the last declared ImmutableTable
This means for a join only the last ImmutableTable will be locked during the select.

top

public TableSelect<E> top(int top)
Description copied from interface: TableSelect
The join will return only the given number of top rows as result.

If TableSelect.skip(int) is applied also, this counts from the start after the skipped rows of the result.
